result.execSummary:
The defendant Corey L Day was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Credit Card-Fraudulent Use (<=$2500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.41(5)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 2:46 pm [Clerk SH] (Case was scheduled for STC)
[Reserve Judge Sarah O'Brien presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Corey L Day in court with Attorney Elizabeth F. Svehlek. ADA Monica J. Hall appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Constitutional rights given; plea of "No Contest" entered on Counts #1 & #2; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, orders JOC entered.

On Count #1, the Court sentences Defendant to:
--serve 6 months in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber/Work-Release privileges & no electronic monitoring; IMPOSED & STAYED

On Count #2, the Court sentences Defendant to:
--serve 30 days in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber/Work-Release privileges & no electronic monitoring; IMPOSED & STAYED

and places the Defendant on Probation for 2 years on Ct#1 and 1 year on Ct#2, concurrent, with conditions: 
--To pay costs of $268 (Ct#1)
--To pay $250 DNA Surcharge
--To submit DNA Sample upon demand
--To pay costs of $243 (Ct#2)
